1. install node js to use npm (node package manager)
2. To install react
    npm i -g create-react-app

3. To create first react app, browse to folder having react  and then trigger
    create-react-app app_name

4. Default path : C:\Users\a020844\AppData\Roaming\npm

5. navigate to new app path and run following
    npm start
    
6. App.js under src folder is the main page

7. You can use babeljs.io to run the major piece of code

8. Install bootstrap
    in the folder of the app do following
    npm i bootstrap@4.1.1 (version specified to make sure we are in sync with tutorial)

9. install browser extension "React Developer Tools"
